Hypo Serb Unit’s Non-Performing Loans Peaked at 20%, Beta Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-08-22T08:22:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/hypo-serb-unit-s-non-performing-loans-peaked-at-20-beta-says.html
The rate of non-performing loans at
the Serbian unit of Hypo Alpe-Adria-Bank International AG has
peaked at 20 percent and is expected to improve this year,  Beta 
newswire reported, citing Vladimir Cupic, the unit’s chief.  The bank adopted more conservative lending policies last
year and plans to open another 20 to 25 offices in the country
where it currently operates 40, Cupic was quoted as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  